# Bench-specific
# Dry-run, stage-gate, mock, and dev tag JSONLs stay local — they're calibration
# artifacts, not part of the registered analysis. The registered run's raw data
# (and judge data) IS published per Methodology Lockdown #9 and §Reproducibility.
data/raw/*.jsonl
data/raw/*.json
!data/raw/.gitkeep
!data/raw/*-registered.jsonl
!data/raw/judge-*-registered.jsonl
# Same logic for derived results: registered-run analysis outputs are published.
data/results/*.html
# Corpus embedding caches — large (~160 MB for SciFact), re-derivable from corpus + provider API.
data/cache/

# Local-only working dirs
.loopgain-bench-scratch/
